== Research 

== Peripheral Venous Pressure Signal
This project has been my main focus of PhD research. We are trying to correlate the fluid status of a patient with Peripheral Venous Pressure (PVP) signal. Some elementary results have shown promising results that PVP signal is able to distinguish between dehydrated and hydrated patients. We have also developed an unsupervised algorithm based on [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kalman_filter Kalman filter] and [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hidden_Markov_model hidden Markov model (HMM)] that can detect anomalous segments of PVP signal recording. \n
- ``Unsupervised Anomaly Detection in Peripheral Venous Pressure Signals with Hidden Markov Models" - \[*Under Review*] \[[https://github.com/mahayat/ADPDUPVPS GitHub]]
